peg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F98%2Fef%2F4ee265be4bd1973c81bcf40d5cd1%2Fmorgana-o-reilly-arnas-fedaravicius-christian-friedel-dom-hetrakul-lalisa-manobal.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+100/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F98%2Fef%2F4ee265be4bd1973c81bcf40d5cd1%2Fmorgana-o-reilly-arnas-fedaravicius-christian-friedel-dom-hetrakul-lalisa-manobal.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+100/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F98%2Fef%2F4ee265be4bd1973c81bcf40d5cd1%2Fmorgana-o-reilly-arnas-fedaravicius-christian-friedel-dom-hetrakul-lalisa-manobal.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+100/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F98%2Fef%2F4ee265be4bd1973c81bcf40d5cd1%2Fmorgana-o-reilly-arnas-fedaravicius-christian-friedel-dom-hetrakul-lalisa-manobal.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+100/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F98%2Fef%2F4ee265be4bd1973c81bcf40d5cd1%2Fmorgana-o-reilly-arnas-fedaravicius-christian-friedel-dom-hetrakul-lalisa-manobal.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/1920x1080+0+100/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F98%2Fef%2F4ee265be4bd1973c81bcf40d5cd1%2Fmorgana-o-reilly-arnas-fedaravicius-christian-friedel-dom-hetrakul-lalisa-manobal.jpg" class="img" alt="Morgana O&amp;#039;Reilly, Arnas Fedaravičius, Christian Friedel, Dom Hetrakul and Lalisa Manobal play resort workers in Season 3 of The White Lotus." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 &lt;br&gt;Morgana O'Reilly, Arnas Fedaravičius, Christian Friedel, Dom Hetrakul and Lalisa Manobal play resort workers in Season 3 of &lt;em&gt;The White Lotus.&lt;/em&gt;                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Fabio Lovino/HBO                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Check out what &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/culture/" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NPR&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt; is watching, reading and listening to this weekend:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🍿 Movies:&lt;/strong&gt; In his documentary &lt;em&gt;SLY LIVES! (aka The Burden of Black Genius)&lt;/em&gt;, Questlove explores the &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/02/10/nx-s1-5290223/questlove-sly-stone-black-genius" target="_blank"&gt;alienation of success&lt;/a&gt;, particularly for Black artists, through the life and genius of funk trailblazer Sly Stone.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; 📺 TV:&lt;/strong&gt; In the age of streaming and prestige TV, it can be easy to forget how many great shows air on old-school TV networks. Luckily, Pop Culture Happy Hour has your &lt;a href="https://one.npr.org/?sharedMediaId=1230674441:1266225199" target="_blank"&gt;guide to network TV&lt;/a&gt;. If streaming's more your thing, though, don't forget to catch a new season of &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/02/13/nx-s1-5295015/the-white-lotus-season-3-thailand-review" target="_blank"&gt;&lt;em&gt;The White Lotus&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt; this weekend.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;📚 Books:&lt;/strong&gt; Bill Gates is used to envisioning what our future could look like. His newest memoir, &lt;em&gt;Source Code: My Beginnings&lt;/em&gt;, looks back in time. He sat down with &lt;em&gt;All Things Considered&lt;/em&gt; to &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/02/10/g-s1-47679/bill-gates-microsoft-book-source-code-memoir" target="_blank"&gt;reflect on his youth&lt;/a&gt; and beginnings.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;🎵 Music:&lt;/strong&gt; On this week's list of songs our music editors can't stop playing, the tracks touch on &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/02/11/1230674437/all-songs-considered-the-contenders-vol-4" target="_blank"&gt;themes of unity, resilience and the power&lt;/a&gt; of close connections.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;❓Quiz: &lt;/strong&gt;I've had fun this week filling in for newsletter writer Brittney Melton, until I got a "tolerable" 8/11 on this week's quiz. &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/02/14/g-s1-48486/elon-musk-donald-trump-super-bowl-dogs-kendrick-lamar" target="_blank"&gt;How will you do&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-48672" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 4896;         --source-height: 2754;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4896x2754+0+255/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2Fbc%2F49%2F8e70cb924243810bf939fba8740b%2Fgettyimages-2155105383.jpg" class="img" alt="The green Duolingo owl on a phone screen and background behind it." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Duolingo announced the death of its owl mascot, Duo, this week. He was known for his snarky social media presence and sometimes-threatening way of reminding people to do their daily language lessons.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          NurPhoto/via Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;Duo Keyshauna Renee Lingo, the bright green owl mascot that urges Duolingo app users to practice learning their foreign languages every day, is dead. What's &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/02/13/nx-s1-5295597/duolingo-owl-mascot-death" target="_blank"&gt;behind this viral marketing campaign&lt;/a&gt;?&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Be careful if you're planning a grand romantic gesture today. Despite their best intentions, these NPR listeners &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2025/02/10/nx-s1-5292285/valentines-day-gift-fail-stories" target="_blank"&gt;ended up with a Valentine's Day fail&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;Eating yogurt regularly could &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/sections/shots-health-news/2025/02/14/nx-s1-5295042/yogurt-colon-cancer-diet-health" target="_blank"&gt;lower your risk&lt;/a&gt; of certain types of aggressive colon cancer, according to a new study.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/g-s1-2467/obed-manuel"target="_blank"   &gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;Obed Manuel&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
